<span id="freeTextContainer14941916711862694273">Oh yes, I totally want to read about all the affairs Genji, the &quot;shining&quot; prince, had with dozens of other women. Not to mention most of these women looked like his mother in some way or another. (Freud would be esctatic.) One of these women wasn&apos;t even a woman at all, but a small child he pretty much abducted. Of course, this young girl looked like his mother.<br/><br/>The fact that this is the first true psychological novel in the world is interesting, it really is. But just because it is so doesn&apos;t mea</span>
  <span id="freeText14941916711862694273" style="display:none">Oh yes, I totally want to read about all the affairs Genji, the "shining" prince, had with dozens of other women. Not to mention most of these women looked like his mother in some way or another. (Freud would be esctatic.) One of these women wasn't even a woman at all, but a small child he pretty much abducted. Of course, this young girl looked like his mother.<br /><br />The fact that this is the first true psychological novel in the world is interesting, it really is. But just because it is so doesn't mean it's interesting as a story.</span>
